Players and friends of Ibadan Golf Club have been promised an exciting time at the prestigious club when it hosts the 12th Lady Captain’s inaugural tournament on June 17 and 18. During the tournament, the new lady captain, Queen Mowah, would be unveiled to members and friends of the club in a ceremony that involves foods and drinks. According to the club, over 200 golfers from Aba Golf Club, Benin Golf Club, Python and Port Harcourt Golf Club from Rivers State and other notable golf clubs nationwide are expected to participate in the two-day golfing outing, which is streamlined to be unique. Attesting to the competence of the new lady captain, elegant lady golfer, Sumbo Oshile, described Queen Mowah as ‘a lady captain with a large heart in the state of the big heart.’ “Queen Mowah is evidently a born-natural seasoned organiser, who is courteous, charitable, caring, compassionate, coordinated, considerate, confident golfer,” said Oshile, whom is a former lady captain of both Ibadan Golf Club and Tiger Golf Club. Explaining why the new lady captain deserved to be celebrated, Oshile noted that Queen Mowah has headed many planning committees in the IGCC and had successfully, over the years, executed many golf tournaments and has done her best to enhance development of golf at the grassroots.